# Java Package Convention

All Java classes use `org.termx` as the root package.

## Package Structure

- API contracts: `org.termx.ts.*`, `org.termx.sys.*`, `org.termx.snomed.*`, etc. (termx-api module)
- Core infrastructure: `org.termx.core.*` (termx-core module)
- Feature modules: `org.termx.<feature>.*` (e.g., `org.termx.terminology.*`, `org.termx.wiki.*`)
- Application: `org.termx.*` (termx-app module)

Examples:
- `org.termx.ts.codesystem.CodeSystem` (API DTO)
- `org.termx.core.auth.SessionInfo` (core infrastructure)
- `org.termx.terminology.terminology.codesystem.CodeSystemService` (feature implementation)

**Note:** External dependencies from `com.kodality.commons.*` and `com.kodality.kefhir.*` remain unchanged.
